    <dlgPart>
      <portrait>Varro</portrait>
      <speaker_name>Varro</speaker_name>
      <npc_text>“If an accident were to befall you, would it lessen the Gods’ ability to express their wishes? Had Meru had you killed when you requested that audience, would he still be alive?”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“He would but not for long. I *am* an agent of Gods' will but should I fall another will take my place and deliver a very different message.”</text>
          <def_link>9352</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>9351</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait>Varro</portrait>
      <speaker_name>Varro</speaker_name>
      <npc_text>“Is this a threat?”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“A fair warning. Meru wished for the Gods to return. They did. Unfortunately for Meru, they chose me to rule in their name, not him. Accept it and nothing else would have to change. Oppose it in any way and the next *message* will rain fire and brimstone.”</text>
          <def_link>9353</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>9352</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait>Varro</portrait>
      <speaker_name>Varro</speaker_name>
      <npc_text>“Nothing else would have to change? That's your carrot?” Varro asks quietly. “We both know that it doesn't work this way. If what you say is true, there will be a great deal of changes before the Gods are satisfied.”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>[persuasion]“The Gods want to rule from the shadows, so we'll keep the changes to the minimum. We'll rely on the Inquisition to keep order, so you won't be left out. Who knows, I might even arrange a few miracles to make your job easier.”</text>
          <def_link>9358</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick>
            <string>aod.persuasion &gt;= 9</string>
          </checksOnClick>
          <linksOnClick>
